{"actual_usd":0.15815500000000002,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":158,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31157,"reply":"\"No—always the Son.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square, the chain at the well giving one small clink in the morning.* \"His baptism wasn't God adopting a regular man into sonship. It was more like a revealing—'this is my beloved Son'—not 'this man has now become my Son.'\"\n\n\"As for becoming divine—He didn't.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of the folded note in my pocket, thinking how easy it is for people to slide Jesus either downward into just-a-man or upward into something that never really came among us.* \"Christianly speaking, He was always divine. The claim is that the eternal Son took on flesh; not that a non-divine human got upgraded later.\"","rolling_24h_usd":39.70494500000003,"run_id":"6db89cc4-fd80-49ef-83e0-a3f7f98c8255"}
